DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "contextFiniteSolutionSets.pl", "contextForm.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("FiniteSolutionSets"); Context()->variables->are(z=>'Real'); Context()->flags->remove("NumberCheck"); $answer = Formula("{12.4}");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Solve the equation [`-7.3+z=5.1`] for [`z\text{.}`]
[_]{$answer}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION Our goal is to remove that [`-7.3`] from the left side. Since that negative number is being _added_ to [`z\text{,}`] we could _subtract_ [`-7.3`] from both sides.
[```\newcommand{\subtractright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}-#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} -7.3+z\amp=5.1\\ -7.3+z\subtractright{(-7.3)}\amp=5.1\subtractright{(-7.3)}\\ z\amp=12.4 \end{aligned} ```]
It is just as effective to add positive [`7.3`] to each side.
[```\newcommand{\addright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}+#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} -7.3+z\amp=5.1\\ -7.3+z\addright{7.3}\amp=5.1\addright{7.3}\\ z\amp=12.4 \end{aligned} ```]
We should check the solution by substituting [`12.4`] in for [`z`] in the original equation:
[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} -7.3+z\amp=5.1\\ -7.3+(\substitute{12.4})\amp\wonder{=}5.1\\ 5.1\amp\confirm{=}5.1 \end{aligned} ```]
The solution [`12.4`] is checked, and the solution set is [`\{12.4\}\text{.}`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
